      <div class="msgContentFrame">You can't use if/then logic like that in a macro, otherwise you could write a script that would basically run your priorities/rotation for you.  The most you can do is check some basic conditions, area flyable/not flyable, target friendly/not friendly, target alive/dead, focus exists/does not exist, do you even have a target, etc. <br /> <br />Warriors used to, back in early BC I think, use a /castrandom macro to try and hit their abilities as they came off cooldown.  Shortly thereafter, /castrandom was changed to break if it tried to use an ability that was still on CD.</div>
