      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Mozared wrote:</div><div class="orig">Slap me silly if I'm saying something stupid here, but what about a simple <br /> <br /><i>#showtooltip Devastate <br />/cast Revenge <br />/cast Devastate</i> <br /> <br />... ? <br /> <br />Seems like it would work to me? First, the macro attempts to cast Revenge. If Revenge isn't up, it won't work and simply skip the step and go to /cast Devastate. If Revenge IS up, it should cast Revenge and give you an error on Devastate since it can't cast that because of the GCD.</div></div> <br />Wouldn't work. <br /> <br />The game would constantly be giving you a &quot;you can't use that yet&quot; message instead of moving onto the next ability. <br /> <br />There's really no way to do this without a castsequence macro, like rogues used to use for Riposte/SS. Basically use this: <br /> <br /><i>#show Revenge <br />/castsequence reset=5 Devastate, Revenge, Devastate, Devastate</i> <br /> <br />If you spam that, you should have no problem hitting all of your Revenges as they pop up.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm"><a href="HTTP://dictionary.reference.com/browse/theophany" rel="external nofollow" title="dictionary.reference.com/browse/theophany"><b>The·oph·a·ny</b></a> <i>(thē-ŏf'ə-nē)</i> <br />An appearance of a god to a human; a divine manifestation. <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://us.battle.net/wow/en/character/draka/korz/" rel="external nofollow" title="us.battle.net/wow/en/character/draka/korz/">Rogue</a> | <a href="HTTP://us.battle.net/wow/en/character/draka/k%C3%B4rz/" rel="external nofollow" title="us.battle.net/wow/en/character/draka/kôrz/">Mage</a> | <a href="/forum.html?forum=214&amp;mid=1284152030146222020" rel="external" title="wow.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=214&amp;mid=1284152030146222020">PvP 101</a></span></div></div>
