      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Overlord Theophany wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">AstarintheDruid wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Overlord Theophany wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Mozared wrote:</div><div class="orig">Slap me silly if I'm saying something stupid here, but what about a simple <br /> <br /><i>#showtooltip Devastate <br />/cast Revenge <br />/cast Devastate</i> <br /> <br />... ? <br /> <br />Seems like it would work to me? First, the macro attempts to cast Revenge. If Revenge isn't up, it won't work and simply skip the step and go to /cast Devastate. If Revenge IS up, it should cast Revenge and give you an error on Devastate since it can't cast that because of the GCD.</div></div> <br />Wouldn't work. <br /> <br />The game would constantly be giving you a &quot;you can't use that yet&quot; message instead of moving onto the next ability. <br /> <br />There's really no way to do this without a castsequence macro, like rogues used to use for Riposte/SS. Basically use this: <br /> <br /><i>#show Revenge <br />/castsequence reset=5 Devastate, Revenge, Devastate, Devastate</i> <br /> <br />If you spam that, you should have no problem hitting all of your Revenges as they pop up.</div></div> <br /> <br />That would work if Revenge only had the 5 sec CD, but it's also conditional on a block, parry, or dodge.  It's entirely possible for a bad RNG string to cause the macro to hang for several seconds waiting for Revenge to light up.  It also doesn't allow for Shield Slam (6 sec CD, CD reset with Sword and Board procs.)  With the threat modifier on Shield Slam, that should actually be your first priority.  Then Revenge if it's up, then Devastate.  Heroic Strike if you have a lot of excess rage.</div></div> <br />Yeah, I never said it was a good idea, or that you should use it. I said that that would work. <br /> <br />Read the post next time, bro.</div></div> <br /> <br />I did, bro, I was just pointing out that Revenge has another conditional requirement.  That way, if bad RNG causes the OP to take several unblocked hits in a row, he knows why his macro isn't working.  The second part was pointing out that, despite Shield Slam doing the least damage of the three abilities, it causes the most threat. <br /></div>
